UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219969090071S
AB  - This paper derives optimal trade policies for exporting and importing countries when a market is imperfectly competitive and firms are internationally owned. It is shown that an increase in foreign ownership of firms lowers both the optimal export subsidy of the exporting country and the optimal import tariff of the importing country at the same rate. Foreign ownership also affects the distribution of world welfare between countries. However, it does not affect trade patterns and firm values.
